    • Field Detail

      • levelNodes

        java.util.List<java.util.Map<Node,Node>> levelNodes
        A List in which each item corresponds to a level. An item is a Map that represents the member function for nodes of the current level, as (node, node-on-the-next-level-this-node-belongs-to). The last level should have all values null.

      • theLevels

        java.util.List<java.util.Map<Node,Graph>> theLevels
        A List in which each item at position corresponds to a level. The first element of the list is an empty Map (for easier reading of code). An item is a Map that links a Node from the level above to a subgraph at the current level which corresponds to that Node.
